# Memory leak follow-ups (from GreasyFork discussion 335638, after fixing the Filter Box remount leak — ADR 0010)

Candidates surfaced while investigating the reported unbounded WebExtensions RSS growth
(370MB → 7.86GB over 20-24h). Only the Filter Box remount leak (ADR 0010, [[Filter Box
Remount Leak]] in CONTEXT.md) has been confirmed and fixed. The rest are not yet actioned:

- **`descriptions_observer` (`faction/index.ts:557`)** — unconfirmed, needs verification.
  A `MutationObserver` recreated on every `process_page()` call (same trigger as the fixed
  leak) and never disconnected. Its callback doesn't close over any per-navigation element
  (only calls `wait_for_element`/`setup_war_features` fresh each time), and an active
  `MutationObserver` typically holds only a weak reference to its target node — so if Torn
  replaces `#faction_war_list_id` on every tab switch (as it does for `.members-list`/
  `.faction-war`), the old node and its dangling observer likely become collectible
  together without further action. Whether this actually holds depends on whether Torn
  ever *reuses* the same node across navigations instead of replacing it (would stack
  redundant observers on one node, firing `setup_war_features` repeatedly — harmless
  functionally thanks to its own `data-ffscouter-initialized` guard, but wasteful). Verify
  empirically (heap snapshot across repeated tab switches) before deciding whether this
  needs the same track-and-disconnect treatment as ADR 0010.
- **Three redundant SPA-navigation-detection mechanisms** — ruled out as a leak (each
  registers a fixed set of listeners once per document, doesn't compound), but a real
  architecture inconsistency worth consolidating: the Navigation API / `on_navigation`'s
  `popstate`+`hashchange` fallback (`src/utils/dom.ts:790-812`), and `status-attack`'s own
  independent `pushState`/`replaceState` monkey-patch (`src/features/status-attack/index.ts:224-239`)
  are three separate ways of answering "did navigation happen."
- **Unbounded module-level caches** — real leaks by definition (never evicted for the
  document's lifetime) but bounded by the space of distinct input values and almost
  certainly KB-, not GB-, scale: `bubble_width_cache` (`src/utils/dom.ts:205`) and
  `seenUnknownActivityLabels` (`src/utils/dom.ts:452`). Hygiene-level fix, not urgent.

# React Doctor follow-ups (re-run: v0.5.8, after CSS-modules migration + Fedded/Fallen)

59 warnings total (Bugs 9, Performance 16, Accessibility 14, Maintainability 20).
Run `bun run react-doctor` to re-check. The prop-sync bug
(no-adjust-state-on-prop-change in flight-status) is already fixed. Line numbers
below are post-CSS-modules; confirm each against the code before acting.

Resolved since last baseline (by the CSS-modules migration): `no-inline-exhaustive-style`
on the faction-filter-box `<select>` and that select's `no-tiny-text` (11px) — both moved
into `faction-filter-box.module.css`.

## Maintainability
- Decompose `FFFactionFilterBox` (`src/ui/faction-filter-box.tsx:169`, ~735 lines) and
  `SettingsPanelComponent` (`src/ui/settings-panel.tsx:98`) into section sub-components —
  the deferred decomposition work.
- `only-export-components` ×3: faction-filter-box exports non-components
  (`getFilterBoxHandle`, `DEFAULT_STATE`) and settings-panel exports the `FFSettingsPanel`
  host class — only hurts Fast Refresh, which the userscript build doesn't use. Low priority.
- FALSE POSITIVE — `unused-export: default` ×16 on feature modules: the `default`
  exports are consumed by the `import.meta.glob` discovery in `src/features/index.ts`,
  which react-doctor's static analysis can't see. Do not remove.
- FALSE POSITIVE — `unused-dev-dependency: react-doctor`: it's a CLI tool, not imported.

## Bugs (all warnings, behavior currently correct)
- FALSE POSITIVE — `exhaustive-deps` at `src/shims/react.ts:45,50,86`: these are the
  lazy hook *wrapper* functions in the React shim, not real hook call sites.
- `exhaustive-deps` at `faction-filter-box.tsx:357,388`: real mount-only effects with
  intentional empty deps (suppressed via biome-ignore); review if logic changes.
- `no-initialize-state` at `faction-filter-box.tsx:358`: `collapsed` is seeded from the
  mount effect (loadState) rather than useState initializer — causes one extra render.
- `prefer-useReducer` / `no-cascading-set-state`: `flight-status.tsx:45,57` and
  `info-line.tsx:43` have several related useState/setState calls that could be grouped
  into a reducer.

## Performance
- `rerender-lazy-ref-init` at `faction-filter-box.tsx:198`: `useRef(isMobileView())`
  recomputes every render — use `useRef<…>(null)` + lazy init or `useState(() => …)`.
- `js-combine-iterations` at `faction-filter-box.tsx:766`: the status-options
  `.filter(...).map(...)` (added for the war-mode Fallen exclusion) loops twice over a
  7-element array — trivial; combine into one pass if touching this code.
- `js-batch-dom-css` at `column-population.ts:246-247,266-267`: batch the sequential
  `element.style.*` writes (cssText / class) to avoid repeated layout.
- `js-set-map-lookups` at `ffscouter.ts:67`, `js-combine-iterations` at `storage.ts:128`,
  `async-await-in-loop` (faction/index.ts:540, index.ts:67/83, dom.ts:384, ffcache.ts:277/293):
  pre-existing non-React hot-path nits; low priority.

## Accessibility
- `control-has-associated-label` ×13 (faction-filter-box checkboxes/inputs at
  680,796,803,815,823,836,843,856,864; settings-panel at 218,246,345,354):
  add aria-labels to controls whose visible text isn't programmatically associated.
- `no-tiny-text` ×1 (`info-line.tsx:138`): 11px "Est. Stats" text; bump to ≥12px if it
  doesn't break the Torn-page layout.
